!! Q: Why does the IDE not appear when I view my tiddler?

The IDE renders via a ViewTemplate integration that checks for `rri.type: explide/config`. Make sure:

* The field name is exactly `rri.type` (not `type` or `rri-type`)
* The value is exactly `explide/config`
* The server was restarted after installing the plugin (ViewTemplate is a shadow tiddler)

!! Q: My imported plugin's shadow tiddlers are not showing up. What's wrong?

The plugin must be listed in `tiddlywiki.info` and loaded by the server. Explide reads shadow tiddlers from the wiki store — it cannot import plugins that are not installed. Check that the plugin title in `rri.imported-plugins` matches exactly (e.g., `$:/plugins/rimir/components`).

!! Q: Can I use explide with single-file wikis (no Node.js server)?

Yes. Explide is 100% wikitext with no JS modules or server-side code. It works in any TiddlyWiki environment. However, you need the theme and components plugins installed as dependencies.

